The House member representing Dutsinma Kurfi Federal Constituency of Katsina State under the APC, Armayau Abdulkadir, has reiterated his readiness to tackle the problems of his constituents. Armayau, who said this while speaking with newsmen in Abuja, noted that Nigeria’s health and education sectors were in comatose, noting that they needed urgent attention for the benefit of the masses. He also assured them that he will not divert allocated funds meant for his constituency project in line with his campaign promise. “I will work for the advancement of the constituency. This victory is yours because you promised and fulfilled. It is my turn to reciprocate,” he said. He urged the people of the state to work with Governor Aminu Bello Masari to combat the challenges of banditry in the state. Katsina PDM expels chieftain Katsina PDM expels chieftain Katsina NOA sensitises voters on void vote, peaceful polls Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin